-- CONTROL: a polymorphic Num operator (`add a b = a + b`, inferred `Num a =>`) must
-- STAY dict-routed — its operand never grounds to a concrete primitive, so
-- resolveArithSite leaves the route RNone (no Float stamp).  Instantiated at Int
-- here: if it were mis-stamped Float, `add 2 3` would emit float arith → wrong.
add a b = a + b
main = add 2 3
